ten including mimicry. Etymology The genus name Oenanthe is derived from the Ancient Greek oenos (οίνος) \"wine\" and anthos (ανθός) \"flower\". It refers to the northern wheatear's return to Greece in the spring just as the grapevines blossom. The specific leucopyga is Ancient Greek from leukos, \"white\", and puge, \"rump\". \"Wheatear\" is not derived from \"wheat\" or any sense of \"ear\", but is a 16th-century linguistic corruption of \"white\" and \"arse\", referring to the prominent white rump found in many species. References", "shortSummary": "The white-crowned wheatear, or white-crowned black wheatear (Oenanthe leucopyga) is a wheatear, a small passerine bird that was formerly cl…", "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Red-rumped_wheatear_%28Oenanthe_moesta%29_Kebili.jpg/960px-Red-rumped_wheatear_%28Oenanthe_moesta%29_Kebili.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-oenanthe", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-oenanthe-leucopyga", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-oenanthe", "species": "taxonomy-species-oenanthe-leucopyga"}, "expandable": true, "x": 778.84, "y": 854.3, "z": -336.98}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-oenanthe-leucopyga", "name": "White-crowned wheatear", "latinName": "Oenanthe leucopyga", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "White-crowned wheatear（Oenanthe leucopyga）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如White-crowned wheatear。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": 778.84, "y": 854.3, "z": -330.91}], "links": [{"key": "bird-white-crowned-wheatear-5635e21b__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-oenanthe-leucopyga", "source": "bird-white-crowned-wheatear-5635e21b", "target": "taxonomy-species-oenanthe-leucopyga", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv